+## T-214-01
+
+Patched the fallback preview payload in `src/policy/preview.py` so the preview-unavailable response now keeps `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`. This preserves the reopened human-review fallback state instead of dropping it.
+
+## T-214-02
+
+No separate code change. This is a duplicate of `T-214-01`, and the same fallback payload fix covers it.
+
+## T-214-03
+
+Not applied. This thread points at an outdated diff hunk and asks to revive legacy preview behavior on the current branch. I left that path untouched and did not reintroduce any legacy branch or hint fields.
+
+## T-214-04
+
+Added a regression in `tests/test_preview.py` covering `build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)`. The test now asserts the fallback payload keeps `approval_state="human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review=true`.
+
+## T-214-05
+
+Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback JSON example now matches the corrected payload, including `approval_state: "human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review: true`.
